25:40.874 --> 25:42.793
Calm your ham, I'm gonna bring them back.

25:45.963 --> 25:47.631
Well, clean up this shit.

25:53.470 --> 25:54.471
Urs! Hi?

25:54.555 --> 25:56.932
- Sorry. Have you got a moment?
- Hey, what's up?

25:57.015 --> 26:00.060
Yeah. Yeah. Of course, come in.

26:02.271 --> 26:04.523
It's, it's more than just a fling.

26:05.482 --> 26:06.859
Does Donal know?

26:10.612 --> 26:12.656
- I don't want to hurt him.
- Yeah.

26:14.408 --> 26:15.701
I don't want to lose the kids.

26:15.784 --> 26:17.411
You're not gonna lose the kids.

26:17.494 --> 26:18.495
Just…

26:20.038 --> 26:21.081
How long has it been going on?

26:21.164 --> 26:22.833
Just over a year.

26:23.750 --> 26:25.127
Why are you telling me now?

26:27.421 --> 26:29.131
The prick, Eva.

26:30.424 --> 26:32.134
He found out. He followed me.

26:33.635 --> 26:35.095
Fuck. What?

26:35.179 --> 26:37.222
If I don't end it,
he's gonna tell Donal everything.

26:37.306 --> 26:40.100
And I-I tried.
And I tried, I really tried.

26:41.894 --> 26:43.103
I hate myself.

26:44.313 --> 26:46.273
I just lie, and I cheat.

26:46.356 --> 26:48.567
No. Come here, it's fine. Stop.

26:50.903 --> 26:53.614
I feel like I used to, you know?
When I'm-- When I'm with him.

26:54.865 --> 26:56.116
I feel young.

26:56.992 --> 27:00.204
Part of me that's just been sleepwalking
through life for years is--

27:00.287 --> 27:01.288
is awake again.

27:01.371 --> 27:02.998
- Wow.
- Fuck's sake.

27:03.081 --> 27:05.292
- Jesus Christ, Bibi.
- Sorry. Okay.

27:05.375 --> 27:08.045
First of all, I'm gonna vomit.
You're pathetic.

27:08.128 --> 27:10.797
And secondly, there's another option.

27:10.881 --> 27:12.591
- Shut up.
- Why? We need her help anyway.

27:12.674 --> 27:14.259
- Shut up, Bibi.
- What's she talking about?

27:14.343 --> 27:17.137
Second option is we lance
the seeping boil that is the prick.

27:18.096 --> 27:19.264
We get rid of him.

27:19.848 --> 27:21.892
Get rid of him? What are you on about?

27:21.975 --> 27:23.393
Fucking hell.

27:24.228 --> 27:25.312
Hang on.

27:25.395 --> 27:27.940
We just want to give nature
a helping hand.

27:33.570 --> 27:35.948
Are you out of your fucking mind?

27:36.031 --> 27:37.866
Yeah. May-- I don't know. Maybe.

27:38.575 --> 27:41.578
No. No. I'm sorry.
You're not dragging me into this.

27:41.662 --> 27:42.996
No fucking way.

27:46.667 --> 27:47.960
Am I-- Am I culpable now?

27:49.086 --> 27:52.631
Because you told me ab--
You can't do this.

27:52.714 --> 27:56.635
You're gonna land yourselves,
and me, in jail or worse.

27:56.718 --> 27:58.929
We're gonna poison him, Ursula,
with or without your consent,

27:59.012 --> 28:00.514
and we have no intention
of getting caught.

28:00.597 --> 28:03.684
And how exactly are you planning
on doing that?

28:05.602 --> 28:06.645
Death cap.

28:07.855 --> 28:08.856
Are you insane?

28:10.315 --> 28:11.900
What about Blanaid?

28:13.527 --> 28:14.987
What-- What about Grace?

28:15.070 --> 28:18.198
We're gonna do it on liver day.
Only the prick eats it.

28:18.282 --> 28:21.201
That's why we need your help. We just
don't know how to extract the poison.

28:21.285 --> 28:25.914
The first signs of death cap poisoning
are vomiting and diarrhea.

28:26.874 --> 28:29.209
He'll go to A&E, and they'll do tests,

28:29.293 --> 28:32.212
and they'll find amanitin in his blood,
and then they'll call the police.

28:32.296 --> 28:34.590
And then, when he dies
between three and five days later,

28:34.673 --> 28:36.884
they'll be searching for the idiots
who poisoned him.

28:36.967 --> 28:41.471
See? This is why we need your help.
What would you recommend instead?

28:43.557 --> 28:44.558
Urs, we--

28:45.434 --> 28:47.936
Great. That's great.

29:09.208 --> 29:11.668
All right, that's me off
to my night shift, Urs.

29:11.752 --> 29:13.253
Have fun at Eva's tomorrow.

29:22.804 --> 29:23.805
Hey.

29:27.100 --> 29:30.229
- Do you want a bottle opener for that?
- No, I brought that. That's a screw cap.

29:30.312 --> 29:31.313
Classy.

29:31.396 --> 29:32.606
Slut.

29:35.317 --> 29:37.569
What? She was being a judgy bitch.

29:47.496 --> 29:50.958
Hey! Oh, I'll watch next time.
Okay? Catch.

29:52.376 --> 29:53.544
Help.

29:56.797 --> 29:58.924
- Hi.
- Hey. Oh, hi. I wasn't expecting to--

29:59.007 --> 30:01.134
Lemon meringue pie. It has a biscuit base,

30:01.218 --> 30:03.136
and I didn't have time
to make pastries, sorry.

30:03.220 --> 30:05.389
You can't beat this woman's pies.
Pastry or not.

30:05.472 --> 30:07.057
Is it okay? I tried calling.

30:07.140 --> 30:09.309
Yeah, of course.
It's just, you're not usually--

30:09.393 --> 30:10.602
It was John Paul's idea.

30:12.646 --> 30:13.647
Hey, hon.

30:14.314 --> 30:16.692
Okay, she'll be better at this.
We can do this.

30:17.734 --> 30:18.902
No Donal today?

30:19.570 --> 30:20.571
He's working.

30:21.613 --> 30:24.491
That's a shame.
Poor Donal, always missing out.

30:24.575 --> 30:26.201
Yeah.

30:26.285 --> 30:27.286
Okay.

30:33.584 --> 30:35.169
- Lamb?
- I have lots. Thanks.

30:35.252 --> 30:37.087
When's the cabin getting sorted, JP?

30:37.171 --> 30:40.424
The insurance company is being thorny,
but they'll pay out.

30:40.507 --> 30:44.720
Suspicious bloody terriers.
Mammy's very upset.

30:44.803 --> 30:47.181
Well… I had two photo albums in there.

30:47.264 --> 30:49.391
Oh, God. I'm so sorry, Grace.

30:49.474 --> 30:53.187
Yeah, only holiday snaps
of Blanaid when she was little

30:53.270 --> 30:56.023
and others I can't remember,
but photos I can't replace, you know?

30:56.106 --> 30:57.316
And my Rolex

30:57.399 --> 30:59.818
and the stereo system
and the wide-screen TV.

30:59.902 --> 31:03.530
He's making light of it,
but he was really shocked.

31:03.614 --> 31:06.325
We're just counting our blessings
that he wasn't actually in there.

31:06.408 --> 31:09.077
Grace, thank God
you and Blanaid weren't there.

31:09.578 --> 31:11.580
I mean, Christ,
it doesn't bear thinking about.

31:11.663 --> 31:13.832
Yeah.
Well, we were at the concert, so…

31:16.043 --> 31:17.961
Can you pass the green beans
over there?

31:19.296 --> 31:20.297
More sauce?

31:21.590 --> 31:22.716
No.

31:24.551 --> 31:28.055
I'll have some. Thank you.

31:30.140 --> 31:31.934
- It's mint.
- You won't like it, pet.

31:33.894 --> 31:34.895
What is that?

31:34.978 --> 31:36.605
Ursula!

31:36.688 --> 31:37.731
Are you doing then?

31:37.814 --> 31:38.941
- Come on!
- Why?

31:39.024 --> 31:41.235
- No!
- Becka! Becka! Becka!

31:41.318 --> 31:43.695
Why do we have to do it?

31:43.779 --> 31:45.405
'Cause what would Dad say if we didn't?

31:45.489 --> 31:47.407
He would say…

31:48.575 --> 31:50.494
"This country

31:50.577 --> 31:56.291
was made a free republic
on Easter Sunday in 1916.

31:56.375 --> 31:57.751
Do the poem, girleen!"

31:59.127 --> 32:00.212
Drunk. Drunk and all.

32:02.130 --> 32:05.300
"We knew enough to know that dre"--
I've forgotten--

32:05.384 --> 32:07.761
forgotten the whole thing. I'm so sorry.

32:07.845 --> 32:09.555
- You know this.
- Okay. "We--

32:11.348 --> 32:13.559
We knew their dream; enough
To know they dreamed"--

32:13.642 --> 32:15.769
Don't you laugh-- "And are dead."

32:15.853 --> 32:17.813
- Go!
- Oh, it's me.

32:17.896 --> 32:23.193
"And what if-- What if excess of love
Bewildered them till they died?"

32:23.277 --> 32:24.611
Urs!

32:24.695 --> 32:27.656
- Go on.
-"Write it out in a verse--"

32:27.739 --> 32:29.366
"MacDonagh and MacBride."

32:29.449 --> 32:31.201
Yes! She knows it.

32:31.285 --> 32:33.787
Come on! Go on.

32:33.871 --> 32:35.330
"And…"

32:35.414 --> 32:36.874
- And to…
-"Connolly!"

32:36.957 --> 32:38.584
- Yay!
- And…

32:38.667 --> 32:40.294
Look at her, so happy with ourselves.

32:40.377 --> 32:42.087
And… And…

32:42.171 --> 32:43.714
- And…
-"And…"

32:43.797 --> 32:44.631
"Pearse."

32:44.715 --> 32:45.716
Yes!

32:45.799 --> 32:50.387
"Now, and in time to be,
Wherever green is worn--

32:50.470 --> 32:52.347
- Are changed…
- Changed…

32:52.431 --> 32:55.184
- Come on. Changed…
- Are changed…

32:55.267 --> 32:59.646
"Utterly: A terrible beauty is born."

32:59.730 --> 33:00.731
Come on!

33:10.157 --> 33:12.951
- Mommy?
- Oh, I'm sorry, honey.

33:13.035 --> 33:15.579
- Too loud?
- It's like having a train in my head.

33:15.662 --> 33:17.915
It's like a train in your head. I'm sorry.

33:17.998 --> 33:19.458
Sorry, Michael.

33:20.626 --> 33:23.462
Like an IRA meeting.

33:24.213 --> 33:26.089
Awful.

33:26.173 --> 33:27.841
But we have lovely voices, though, right?

33:27.925 --> 33:30.177
- Yeah, but noisy mammies.
- Noisy mammies?

33:31.553 --> 33:33.138
Drinky mammies.

33:34.306 --> 33:35.307
Not all mammies.

33:35.390 --> 33:37.226
- Is there any more meat, Mammy?
- I'll just go.

33:37.309 --> 33:39.061
Okay. So, take those.

33:40.187 --> 33:42.147
Don't--
Don't get the foils all over my garden.

33:42.898 --> 33:44.274
Do you want some more?

33:45.984 --> 33:48.153
- No. No.
- I'm just giving…

33:48.237 --> 33:50.197
Yeah, that's Easter.
I love the way you've always made--

33:50.280 --> 33:53.951
…to get lots of animals.
